sentences the heretic
Gerard Breuil

6
00:02:57,975 --> 00:03:01,650
to be burnt at the stake,
along with all his writings,

7
00:03:02,415 --> 00:03:05,168
for straying from the way
of Our Lord

8
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:08,811
and translating the work
of the heretic Averroes"

9
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:39,693
D E S T l N Y

10
00:06:07,495 --> 00:06:08,928
Joseph...

11
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:10,853
your mother is dead

12
00:06:11,255 --> 00:06:12,210
Calm down

13
00:06:12,415 --> 00:06:14,770
Go.. l'll take care
of everything

14
00:06:35,335 --> 00:06:38,247
Andalusia - 12th century

15
00:06:39,855 --> 00:06:41,288
Long live Caliph Mansur!

16
00:06:43,175 --> 00:06:44,528
Long live Caliph Mansur!

17
00:06:50,095 --> 00:06:52,290
Long live the victor
of Alarcos!

18
00:06:54,895 --> 00:06:56,294
You praise him,
like these infidels?

19
00:06:56,855 --> 00:07:00,165
l have orders:
flatter him until he bursts

20
00:07:07,615 --> 00:07:08,411
Join in!

21
00:07:32,575 --> 00:07:33,690
l'll give you 5 dinars

22
00:07:33,975 --> 00:07:37,445
Are you joking?
This book comes from Baghdad!

23
00:07:37,815 --> 00:07:40,409
The Caliph would pay

24
00:07:42,855 --> 00:07:43,731
l'll buy it

25
00:07:44,215 --> 00:07:47,013
lf l don't buy it for the Caliph'
library, he'll slay me

26
00:07:48,215 --> 00:07:50,604
l need it for my studies.
l can barely

27
00:07:50,815 --> 00:07:51,691
afford it

28
00:07:55,695 --> 00:07:56,684
For your studies?

29
00:07:57,055 --> 00:07:58,170
Then take it. lt's yours

30
00:08:03,295 --> 00:08:05,604
l'll let you have it
for 7 dinars

31
00:08:07,135 --> 00:08:08,568
All l have is five

32
00:08:10,575 --> 00:08:11,724
You've earned it, wretch

33
00:08:15,175 --> 00:08:17,484
Where can l find Averroes,
the High Judge?

34
00:08:19,215 --> 00:08:21,251
He's my teacher.
l'll take you to him

35
00:08:24,095 --> 00:08:25,972
Wasting such blue eyes
on a boy..

36
00:08:26,175 --> 00:08:27,574
how unfair!

37
00:08:29,495 --> 00:08:32,009
Eat! You're all skin
and bones!

38
00:08:33,015 --> 00:08:34,494
There's enough for an army!

39
00:08:34,695 --> 00:08:36,811
She complains that l'm stingy

40
00:08:37,015 --> 00:08:38,733
but she feeds the whole
neighborhood

41
00:08:40,015 --> 00:08:42,734
lf it weren't for me,
you'd all look like him!

42
00:08:43,095 --> 00:08:44,369
Our eyes would turn blue?

43
00:08:46,935 --> 00:08:49,927
Don't take another bite.
Manuela will put a curse

44
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:53,408
on anyone who doesn't taste
her biscuits

45
00:08:53,815 --> 00:08:56,568
She's challenging me again?
Go get my date bread

46
00:08:56,935 --> 00:08:59,688
Just one bite and she'll
turn green with envy

47
00:08:59,895 --> 00:09:02,011
- Take it to her
- l'm no delivery boy!

48
00:09:02,775 --> 00:09:04,925
l'm the son of the Caliph!

49
00:09:05,175 --> 00:09:06,494
As modest as his father

50
00:09:06,975 --> 00:09:08,374
Tell on me then, Uncle!

51
00:09:08,655 --> 00:09:10,964
lf l were your father,
l'd disown you!

52
00:09:11,295 --> 00:09:12,250
l'm going dancing!

53
00:09:12,535 --> 00:09:15,129
Unbelievable! The Caliph's son
wants to be a dancer!

54
00:09:16,135 --> 00:09:17,204
We call this culture?

55
00:09:17,415 --> 00:09:20,725
At his age, l could dance
for three days straight!

56
00:09:21,135 --> 00:09:24,605
Come to the inn, Blue Eyes, or
they'll stuff you till you burst

57
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:26,524
l should stay

58
